(1)
25-45 Prospect Place, east side, north from East 41st to 43rd Streets, as seen across clearance between 40th and 41st Streets. These buildings, a portion of Tudor City are known as Tudor Tower (No. 25) and Prospect Tower (No. 45), each occupying a complete block front.

March 18, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
A view of No. 25, the Tudor Tower. Shown in the foreground are roofs and cornices of Nos. 311-313 East 40th Street.

August 16, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)
The same as No. 1.

August 16, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.
